nment Board]]. \n\nPrior to trifurcation, the [[Municipal Corporation of Delhi]] was a mega Municipal Corporation, an autonomous body that used to govern 8 of the 9 [[Districts of Delhi]] in the state of [[Delhi]], India. The MCD was among the largest municipal bodies in the world providing civic services to more than an estimated population of 11 million citizens in the capital city. The then unified municipal corporation used to cover an area of 1,397.3 km\u00b2 (539.5 mi\u00b2).<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-11-01/delhi/43591750_1_south-corporation-it-firm-website\n|title=Restart corporation's website, high court tells IT firm\n|newspaper=The Times of India |date=1 November 2013 |accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.mcdonline.gov.in/tri/ndmc_mcdportal/}}\n{{coord missing|Delhi}}\n\n[[Category:Local government in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Municipal corporations in Delhi]]\n[[Category:North Delhi district]]\n\n{{Delhi-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=November 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| name                    = North Delhi Municipal Corporation\n| native_name             = NDMC\n| native_name_lang        = <!-- ISO 639-2 code e.g. \"fr\" for French. If more than one, use {{lang}} instead -->\n| settlement_type         = Urban\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| image_flag              = \n| flag_alt                = \n| image_seal              = \n| seal_alt                = \n| image_shield            = \n| shield_alt              = \n| nickname                =\n| motto                   = \n| image_map               = \n| map_alt                 = \n| map_caption             = \n| pushpin_map             = \n| pushpin_label_position  = \n| pushpin_