= \n| population_footnotes    = \n| population_total        = <!--56 lakh-->\n| population_as_of        = \n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = \n| population_note         = \n| timezone1               = \n| utc_offset1             = \n| timezone1_DST           = \n| utc_offset1_DST         = \n| postal_code_type        = \n| postal_code             = \n| area_code_type          = \n| area_code               = \n| iso_code                = \n| website                 =  {{URL|http://www.mcdonline.gov.in/tri/ndmc_mcdportal/}}  \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n'''North Delhi Municipal Corporation''' (NDMC) is one of the municipal corporations in [[Delhi]], [[India]] created after the former [[Municipal Corporation of Delhi]] was divided into three. Also, it is one of five local bodies in the [[National Capital Territory of Delhi]], the others being [[East Delhi Municipal Corporation]], [[South Delhi Municipal Corporation]], [[New Delhi Municipal Council]] and [[Delhi Cantonment Board]]. \n\nPrior to trifurcation, the [[Municipal Corporation of Delhi]] was a mega Municipal Corporation, an autonomous body that used to govern 8 of the 9 [[Districts of Delhi]] in the state of [[Delhi]], India. The MCD was among the largest municipal bodies in the world providing civic services to more than estimated population of 11 million citizens in the capital city. The then unified municipal corporation used to cover an area of 1,397.3 km\u00b2 (539.5 mi\u00b2).<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-11-01/delhi/43591750_1_south-corporation-it-firm-website\n|title=Restart corporation's website, high court tells IT firm\n|newspaper=The Times of India |date=1 November 2013 |accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.mcdonline.gov.in/tri/ndmc_mcdportal/}}\n{{coord missing|Delhi}}\n\n[[Category:Local government in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Municipal corporations in Delhi]]\n[[Category:North Delhi district]]\n\n{{Delhi-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Gdrged", "label": "safe", "comment": "correction in the line \" than estimated population\"", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Delhi_Municipal_Corporation"}
{"title_page": "United States at the Olympics", "text_new": "{{infobox country at games\n| NOC = USA\n| NOCname = [[United States Olympic & Paralympic Committee]]\n| games = Olympics\n| year = \n| flagcaption = [[Flag of the United States]]\n| oldcode = \n| website = \n| location = \n| competitors = \n| sports = \n| flagbearer = \n| rank = 1\n| gold = 1127\n| silver = 907\n| bronze = 793\n| officials = \n| appearances = \n| app_begin_year = \n| app_end_year = \n| summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=United States|competition=Summer Olympics|begin_year=|end_year= }}\n| winterappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=United States|competition=Winter Olympics|begin_year=|end_year= }}\n| seealso = [[United States at the 1906 Intercalated Games|1906]] Intercalated Games\n}}\n{{See also|United States at the Summer Olympics|United States at the Winter Olympics}}\nThe '''[[United States|United States of America]]''' (USA) has sent athletes to every celebration of the modern [[Olympic Games]] with the exception of the [[1980 Summer Olympics]], during which it led a [[1980 Summer Olympics boycott|boycott]]. The [[United States Olympic & Paralympic Committee]] (USOPC) is the [[National Olympic Committee]] for the United States.\n\nFrom 1896 to 2018, U.S. athletes have won a total of 2,522 medals (1,022 of them gold) at the [[Summer Olympic Games]], more than any other nation, and another 305 at the [[Winter Olympic Games]], the second most behind [[Norway at the Olympics|Norway]]. \n\nThe United States Olympic team remains the only in the world to receive no government funding.<ref>https://www.teamusa.org/about-the-usoc</ref>\n\n== Hosted Games ==\nThe United States has hosted the Games on '''eight''' occasions, more than any other nation, and is planning to host the '''ninth''':\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Games !! Host city !! Dates !! Nations !! Participants !! Events \n|-\n|[[1904 Summer Olympics]] || [[St. Louis]], [[Missouri]] || July 1\u2013November 23 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 12 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 651 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 91 \n|-\n|[[1932 Winter Olympics]] || [[Lake Placid, New York|Lake Placid]], [[New York (state)|New York]] || February 7\u201315 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 17 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 252 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 14\n|-\n|[[1932 Summer Olympics]] || [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] || July 30\u2013August 14 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 37 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1,332 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 117\n|-\n|[[1960 Winter Olympics]] || [[Squaw Valley Ski Resort|Squaw Valley]], [[California]] || February 2\u201320 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 30 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 665 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 27\n|-\n|[[1980 Winter Olympics]] || [[Lake Placid, New York]] || February 13\u201324 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 37 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1,072 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 38\n|-\n|[[1984 Summer Olympics]] || [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] || July 28\u2013August 12 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 140 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 6,829 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 221\n|-\n|[[1996 Summer Olympics]] || [[Atlanta]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] || July 19\u2013August 4 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 197 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 10,318 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 271\n|-\n|[[2002 Winter Olympics]] || [[Salt Lake City]], [[Utah]] || February 8\u201324 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 77 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2,399 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | 78\n|-\n|[[2028 Summer Olympics]] || [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] || July 21\u2013August 6 || style=\"text-align:center;\" | TBA || style=\"text-align:center;\" | TBA || style=\"text-align:center;\" | TBA\n|}\n\n== Medal tables ==\n{{See also|All-time Olympic Games medal count}}\n:''Red border color indicates host nation status.''\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n=== Medals by Summer Games ===\